description: The Mapo Bridge connecting Yonggang-dong, Mapo-gu, Seoul, and Yeouido-dong, Yeongdeungpo-gu, is 1,400m long and 25m wide (6 lanes). It is the fourth bridge on the Han River after the Hannan Bridge. Mapo Bridge started construction in February 1968 and was completed in May 1970. It was named "Seoul Bridge" when it was completed, and was renamed "Mapo Bridge" in 1984.

address: 61-46, Nangye-ro, Seongdong-gu, Seoul 1-72, Geumho-dong 1-ga, Seongdong-gu, Seoul
